  "doc_id": "22788",
  "text": "PH. The IL-6/STAT3 pathway plays pivotal roles in regulating hepatocyte proliferation, at least in the acute liver response after hepatectomy in rodents. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] In addition, the target genes 340 of STAT3 include the anti-apoptotic FLIP, Bcl-2, and Bcl-xL genes, and therefore STAT3 potentially has anti-apoptotic capacity. [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] Hepatocyte apoptosis was undetectable by cleaved caspase 3 in all groups. Therefore, the persistent STAT3 phosphorylation induced by the anti-HMGB1 mAb might have contributed not only to hepatocyte proliferation but also to the prevention of apoptosis.",
